{"id":"fury","term":"Fury","source":"Easton's Bible Dictionary (M.G. Easton, 1897)","html":"<p>As attributed to God, is a figurative expression for dispensing afflictive judgments (<a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Leviticus 26:28\">Lev. 26:28</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Job 20:23\">Job 20:23</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Isaiah 63:3\">Isa. 63:3</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Jeremiah 4:4\">Jer. 4:4</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Ezekiel 5:13\">Ezek. 5:13</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Daniel 9:16\">Dan. 9:16</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Zechariah 8:2\">Zech. 8:2</a>).</p>\n\u0000","refs":["Leviticus 26:28","Job 20:23","Isaiah 63:3","Jeremiah 4:4","Ezekiel 5:13","Daniel 9:16","Zechariah 8:2"]}